## Problem: Where to find Java SDK version 6

### Solution: For SDK version 6, use this link:

- [http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/java-archive-downloads-javase6-419409.html#jdk-6u45-oth-JPR](http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/java-archive-downloads-javase6-419409.html#jdk-6u45-oth-JPR)
- For the official Ubuntu page on installing the Android SDK [try this link](https://help.ubuntu.com/community/AndroidSDK).
- For the official Ubuntu documentation on how to install Java [try this link](https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Java).

**Many people are asking whether JDK 7 will work**.  Professor has said it should work fine, but he's also said he will be using version 6.  This writer intends to use version 6 to save headaches later.

